  <front>
   <head>On the Same Person.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">faster than his costive Brain indites,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">quick Hand in flowing Letters writes;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">His Case appears to Me like honest ,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When he was run away with, by his Legs.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">, give  o'er Himself Command;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Quicken his Senses, or restrain His Hand.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Let Him be kept from Paper, Pen, and Ink:</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">So may He cease to Write, and learn to Think.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
